# 20. Definition of Done for the Component Map

The component map is correctly implemented when:

- all major screens are composed from mapped components
- shared patterns are reused across features
- component naming is consistent
- there is no obvious duplicate component family
- each component has a clear responsibility
- the component tree is scalable for future chat features

---

# 21. Final Goal

After the refactor, Chatvioso should have a component system where:

- chat UI is modular
- layout is reusable
- overlays are consistent
- settings are structured
- new features can be added without UI chaos
- the whole app feels like one cohesive product
